comments.body: Thank you for notifying us, I'm tracking this in https://princeton.service-now.com/nav_to.do?uri=sc_req_item.do?sys_id=800e1d62db184454a4f72736059619cc.  This was apparently an issue in the past, and I don't wish to lose any of the history captured on that ticket.

Don't query all members of a collection to build manifest.

comments.body:
The material for this collection is meant to be very private and only accessible from reading room laptops. The material provided should be the high resolution TIFFs alongside the finding aid. The material hasn't been looked at yet, when it is they'll have an idea of what the overall process will be.

The current recommendation is rather than using the Figgy form they'll add components for each item to the finding aid and Roel will ingest using bulk ingest at the appropriate time.

pas-craft3.title: Add Google Analystics Tracking to Site Template

comments.body:
Setting the config in catalog_controller gives these as options to exhibits; it also has the side effect of making them show up on the main / general search, which I think is okay.

Currently the default field label is "Everything". It will require a data migration to change this; there doesn't appear to be a way to update that label in the UI (it's locked). Requestor proposed "Keyword" as is in LAE and the catalog. However, we've just added an actual keyword field, so "All Fields" might be better.

Note if we do a data migration we likely need to make sure to change blacklight configs for browse categories as well as exhibits.

princeton_ansible.title: does the rails app need passenger
Moving the locator into the machine configs so staging can point at t…

comments.body: @kayiwa I think pas_code will break if the pas role sets up a different database.  That said, since I generally run both together it could work. I think it would be best to have them both ready before merging one.

- [x] recap-staging

- [x] library-staging

- [x] archivesspace-staging

- [x] locator-staging

- [ ] pas-staging

- [ ] bibdata-staging
Locator was moved with this PR: https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/pull/911/files#diff-edb6235875f93679a3e8b701902a44a8R8

@carolyncole I would call them lib-mudd-dbs-staging and lib-mudd-dbs-prod since this is simply a front end for a bunch of database tables. I also wonder if the proxy info is correct? I think they should be proxied from `library.princeton.edu/mudd-dbs/`.  Here is an example page for the faculty table where queries get requested using GET to the following address: https://library.princeton.edu/mudd-dbs/faculties?qname=graduate+alumni+index&LNAME=&FNAME=&dept=

this isn't a big deal but what's the penalty (what's in a name eh?) I already registered the DNS names in the subject (so lib-mudd-staging & lib-mudd-prod) and requested certificates. will the lack of DBS be a problem?
the lack of DBS is not a problem.
End users will only ever see this proxied through the our main domain so the name is arbitrary.
